review_blob: Pours golden with off-white head. Aroma is tropical fruits, citrus, and floral. Taste is citrus, grapefruit, tropical fruits, and pine. Finish has some nice bitterness.
Clear copper colour, , small to medium white head. Aroma: floral, light caramel, bread, citrus Palate : medium body, lively carbonation
beer_name: Brnhr The Drunk Hop - Large Lager

review_blob: alcohol on the aroma, hint of toffee coming through dark amber in colour with no head very sweet on the taste with a slight bitter finish a nice beer a strong one bitter

Orangina yellow colour with a fluffy white head with nice retention. Yeast, malts and grassy hops in the aroma.High carbonation and medium to light body. Taste is medium bitter and light sweet with a long dry finish.
Black with dark brown head . Wonderful smoked malt aroma . Silky smooth . Smoke , dark cocoa , mild roast coffee , mild smoke finish ...full body...great beer
Pale copper in colour with medium head. Aroma is grassy hops, pine tree and resin. Taste like a combination of malts and coniferous trees, some citric notes too
Golden color with a small white head. fruity malty grapefruit hoppy aroma. Fruity malty grapefruit hoppy bitter flavor. Has a fruity malty piney hoppy finish. Clear? ;)
Aroma of coffee, traces of bourbon, ash, some chocolate. Flavour of coffee, bourbon, roast, ash, liquorice, chocolate, bitter finish with some booze. Full-bodied. Good.
Butter, alcohol and caramel. Nice white head. Low bitterness, quite nice malty backbone, sweet, caramel
Baseline for what to expect from a belgian beer. Smooth character with a depth of flavors. Notes of candied sugar and sweet plum tingle the tongue.

Color is dark brownish red. Very little off white head. Aroma and taste are coconut from sugar, caramel, vanilla and malt.. Slight warming on this, but not overpowering. This is an amazing beer. A must try.
beer_name: Brnhr Hop Clan in the Highmalts - Wee Heavy

review_blob: Clear red with a pink frothy head. Fruity candy and light wooden nose. Sweet, medium acidic with notes of soda pop, cherries and other red berries. Light to medium body.
Funky, hazy and delicious. A sweetness to the aroma and the tart is pretty subdued. A bit of funk on the finish, but real nice indeed
Caramel, light grape app : hazy copper white head t/p: full body with sweet and short finish o: good. Smooth it is.

Black body with a small, lacing tan head. Aroma of roasted malt, coffee, chocolate and caramel. Sweet flavor that ends up dry and slightly bitter. Medium to full bodied, oily texture and soft carbonation..
Absolute classic. I just adore the appearance of this beer. Huge, creamy head. A bit of coffee and almost charred malt. Easy to drink
Golden yellow with white head. Nose has banana and belgium yeast. Taste is light bodied- zesty belgium yeast and banana tones. Thin palate
Aroma of grass, grapefruit and coriander seeds with some tropical fruit hints. Taste is grassy with earth and pine, light oak and grapefruit to follow. Hints of pineapple. Light to medium bitterness.
beer_name: Flying Dog Snake Dog IPA (2008 and later)

review_blob: Hazy golden body with a thick white head. Lively carbonation. Great lacing. Aroma of mandarin and lemon. Flavour of lemongrass. Dry finish.

Pours a dark tawny with a small off white head, earthy aroma very complex beer, grain, hay, spice and fruits had a soft carbonation but very lively in the mouth, sweat across the palate excellent example of a trappist
Grassy and pine aroma. Not much head. Very bitter pine flavour and also green grass. Strong taste and aftertaste but pretty straight forward
Pours cloudy yellow with small frothy white top. Aroma is malty, light citrus hops. Taste is creamy mouthfeel, subtle and delicate citrus hops and cereal malts. So nice
beer_name: Brnhr Drink Me Alive! Lager Ale Brew Blend

review_blob: dark red slightly unclear beer with a good tan head. Smells malts, coffee and rye. Tastes great lije barley wine.. Average carbo, full body and a sticky texture
honey, caramel, chocolate; small foamy head; heavy sweetness, medium bitterness, medium sourness; soft carbonation
Golden color. Real detectable aroma... what i can detect is hard to place. Good clean sweet malty flavor with a touch of fine hops. Overall tasty! Good one.
Pure marketing it is like a supermarket cheap beer. Like already said, good for a rock concert, but not more. And not the first beer of the night
Mahogany color with tan head; some lacing. Plum and raisin. Sweet finish.
Mildly malty, and a bit cornish. Medium sweet, almost no bitterness. Refreshing in the sun in summer but nothing more

pours nearly black with a thin coffee colored head; aroma bitter hops, roast coffee, and dark chocolate; taste is initially sweet with chocolate, malt, and alcohol; then becomes bitter with coffee and hops; finish is a dry bitter; excellent I

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Pours dark brown with thick, creamy off-white head. Smells like caramel and bread malts, figs, spice, floral hops, dates, and sugar. Tastes rich, like sweet malt with strong dark fruit, light floral notes, light spice, mildly sweet finish.
thin white head that dissipates. Nose is big oak barrels, funk, juicy fruit snacks, tart lemon. Taste is funk, very tart pulpy lemon, oak barrels, harsh grains. Lingering tartness and bitterness.

Brown with tan head. Aroma is plums, cherry, licorice, spicy Belgian yeast, vanilla and caramel. Slick palate. Aftertaste is rich, fruity, dark chocolate, caramel, cherry, some licorice and lasting spicy finish.
